articles.title: Popular US ski resort changes name to remove offensive word - Stuff.co.nz
articles.description: The renaming of Squaw Valley Ski Resort is one of many efforts nationally to address a history of colonialism and oppression against Native Americans.
articles.content: A popular California ski resort whose name included a derogatory term for Native American women has changed its name to Palisades Tahoe. Resort officials had begun searching for a new name last year … [+2851 chars]
